,\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating documentation needs**\\n\\nI need to look for the documentation that's typically used. I wonder if I can rely on the actor core without external services. It seems like there might be meaningful coverage available with just ActorSystem and Props, which could require no setup. I should investigate the docs more thoroughly, especially focusing on any migration notes about typed actors being removed. It looks like I should do some web searching to find the relevant info.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IOuG4tQlkm61ILcmFt9uyIXi|fc_0e4768216c09fdd5016a40a92aa7b88195a302f0bc2df1b64e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurls=[\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/actors.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/project/migration-guides.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/project/migration-guides.html#typed-actor-removal'\n]\nfor u in urls:\n print('\\nURL',u)\n try:\n  data=urllib.request.urlopen(u,timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n  for term in ['dependency','ActorSystem','TypedActor','removed','Docker','configuration']:\n   i=data.lower().find(term.lower())\n   if i>=0: print(term, data[max(0,i-300):i+500].replace('\\n',' ')[:1000])\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2532, "output": 267, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20207, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782622502664, "responseId": "resp_0e4768216c09fdd5016a40a92701948195b079515646f8d0f0"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_IOuG4tQlkm61ILcmFt9uyIXi|fc_0e4768216c09fdd5016a40a92aa7b88195a302f0bc2df1b64e", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\nURL https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/actors.html\ndependency ef=\"typed/coexisting.html\">coexistence</a>. For new projects we recommend using <a href=\"typed/actors.html\">the new Actor API</a>.</p></div> <h2><a href=\"#module-info\" name=\"module-info\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Module info</h2> <p>To use Classic Actors, add the following dependency in your project:</p><dl class=\"dependency\"><dt>sbt</dt><dd><pre class=\"prettyprint\"><code class=\"language-scala\">val PekkoVersion = \"1.6.0\" libraryDependencies ++= Seq(   \"org.apache.pekko\" %% \"pekko-actor\" % PekkoVersion,   \"org.apache.pekko\" %% \"pekko-testkit\" % PekkoVersion % Test )</code></pre></dd><dt>Maven</dt><dd><pre class=\"prettyprint\"><code class=\"language-xml\">&lt;properties&gt;   &lt;scala.binary.version&gt;2.13&lt;/scala.binary.version&gt; &lt;/properties&gt; &lt;dependen\nActorSystem lassic pertains to the original Actor APIs, which have been improved by more type safe and guided Actor APIs. Pekko Classic is still fully supported and existing applications can continue to use the classic APIs. It is also possible to use the new Actor APIs together with classic actors in the same ActorSystem, see <a href=\"typed/coexisting.html\">coexistence</a>. For new projects we recommend using <a href=\"typed/actors.html\">the new Actor API</a>.</p></div> <h2><a href=\"#module-info\" name=\"module-info\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Module info</h2> <p>To use Classic Actors, add the following dependency in your project:</p><dl class=\"dependency\"><dt>sbt</dt><dd><pre class=\"prettyprint\"><code class=\"language-scala\">val PekkoVersion = \"1.6.0\" libraryDependencies ++= Seq\nconfiguration \"general/remoting.html\" class=\"page\">Location Transparency</a></li>     <li><a href=\"general/jmm.html\" class=\"page\">Apache Pekko and the Java Memory Model</a></li>     <li><a href=\"general/message-delivery-reliability.html\" class=\"page\">Message Delivery Reliability</a></